replies.body:
Oh hey, it's one of these threads. The one that rags about how Gameplay is bad for behaving just like any feedback section in a videogame forum. The one that thinks criticism is the literal devil, and how people whose job is to take feedback are justified in ignoring the space on the official site they've dedicated to it. The one that pretends Boards are the only space on the internet where players show dissatisfaction with League or Riot. The one that complains about Boards being a circlejerk, while simultaneously participating in the exact same hive-mind behavior with false airs of contrarianism. Yep, we definitely needed one more of these threads, because clearly this is such a novel and refreshing angle that will contribute positively to... something.

{{sticker:slayer-jinx-unamused}}

But yeah, if you want to talk about the Boards, go to [Discuss the Boards](https://boards.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/c/community-moderation). This thread discusses the Gameplay sub-Board, but does not actually discuss gameplay, and exists purely to farm upvotes off of the resident anti-Boards circlejerk, which for some reason still appears to be convinced that they're unique, oppressed, and standing up for some grand cause. If nothing else, those Akali threads actually discuss gameplay, so while they are definitely full of toxic behavior, at least they contribute something. This thread, by contrast, contributes nothing, and does not even belong in this space. In other words, OP's thread here is _worse_ than the toxic threads it claims to criticize.
